## CI/CD Pipeline Java Maven Project — Simple Execution Steps

## 1. Create Project Folder

```bash
mkdir java-cicd-app
cd java-cicd-app
```

---

## 2. Create Maven Folder Structure

```bash
mkdir -p src/main/java/com/example
```

Project structure:

```text
java-cicd-app
│── pom.xml
│── Dockerfile
│── Jenkinsfile
└── src
    └── main
        └── java
            └── com
                └── example
                    └── App.java
```

---

## 3. Create Java File

```bash
nano src/main/java/com/example/App.java
```

Paste this:

```java
package com.example;

public class App {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("CI/CD Pipeline Running Successfully");
    }
}
```

Save:

```text
CTRL + O
Enter
CTRL + X
```

---

## 4. Create Simple pom.xml

```bash
nano pom.xml
```

Paste this simple XML:

```xml
<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0">
    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>

    <groupId>com.example</groupId>
    <artifactId>java-cicd-app</artifactId>
    <version>1.0</version>

    <properties>
        <maven.compiler.source>17</maven.compiler.source>
        <maven.compiler.target>17</maven.compiler.target>
    </properties>
</project>
```

---

## 5. Build Maven Project

```bash
mvn clean package
```

This creates:

```text
target/java-cicd-app-1.0.jar
```

---

## 6. Run Java Program

```bash
java -cp target/java-cicd-app-1.0.jar com.example.App
```

Output:

```text
CI/CD Pipeline Running Successfully
```

---

## 7. Create Dockerfile

```bash
nano Dockerfile
```

Paste:

```dockerfile
FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jdk

WORKDIR /app

COPY target/java-cicd-app-1.0.jar app.jar

CMD ["java", "-cp", "app.jar", "com.example.App"]
```

---

## 8. Build Docker Image

```bash
docker build -t java-cicd-app .
```

---

## 9. Run Docker Container

```bash
docker run java-cicd-app
```

Output:

```text
CI/CD Pipeline Running Successfully
```

---

## 10. Initialize Git

```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Java Maven CI CD project"
```

---

## 11. Push to GitHub

Create one empty GitHub repository.

Then run:

```bash
git branch -M main
git remote add origin YOUR_GITHUB_REPO_URL
git push -u origin main
```

---

## 12. Initialize Docker Swarm

```bash
docker swarm init
```

---

## 13. Deploy Using Docker Swarm

```bash
docker service create --name java-service --replicas 2 java-cicd-app
```

---

## 14. Check Service

```bash
docker service ls
```

---

## 15. Create Jenkinsfile

```bash
nano Jenkinsfile
```

Paste:

```groovy
pipeline {
    agent any

    stages {
        stage('Build Maven') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn clean package'
            }
        }

        stage('Build Docker Image') {
            steps {
                sh 'docker build -t java-cicd-app .'
            }
        }

        stage('Deploy Docker Swarm') {
            steps {
                sh 'docker service rm java-service || true'
                sh 'docker service create --name java-service --replicas 2 java-cicd-app'
            }
        }
    }
}
```

---

## 16. Push Jenkinsfile to GitHub

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Added Jenkins pipeline"
git push
```

---

## 17. Jenkins Execution Steps

1. Open Jenkins.
2. Click **New Item**.
3. Enter name: `java-cicd-pipeline`
4. Select **Pipeline**.
5. Click **OK**.
6. Go to **Pipeline** section.
7. Select **Pipeline script from SCM**.
8. SCM: **Git**
9. Paste your GitHub repo URL.
10. Branch: `main`
11. Script Path: `Jenkinsfile`
12. Click **Save**.
13. Click **Build Now**.

---

## Final Output

```text
CI/CD Pipeline Running Successfully
```

This is the simplest full execution from scratch.
